strings.string: \rA titanium door with a slot in it blocks you.\r
\rA steel balcony stops you. Beyond is Finster's mad vision of Earth transformed.\r
\rThe walls are covered with 100 year old pictures.\r
A keyboard pops out, "Input security code."\r
\rThe door is made of steel bars.\r
\rA prisoner runs out crying, "Finster's a heartless android. He'll kill us if we try to leave!"\r
\rYou enter Finster's office. He rises to greet you. Read paragraph 14. He then leaves.\r
"No!" Finster shouts. "You meddlers! You freed them."\r
\rA slope of red rock makes this a tough climb.\r
\rA steel door slides shut behind you.\r
Ambush! Enemies pop up from every side!\r
\rA small closed hatch is in the floor.\r
\rAs you open the hatch mutants attack.\r
\rIt sparks and smokes, blowing itself to pieces.\r
\rAn open hatch is in the floor.\r
\rIt seems possible to connect to the Mindlink with an android's head.\r
\rThe android's head fits, turning the machine on. You put on the Cyber helmet.\r
\rYou must use an android's head to link with the machine.\r
\rYou blank your mind and picture a red/blue pattern.\r
\rYou do not know enough about cyborgs to link with the android's brain. You unhitch yourself.\r
\r\rThe real world fades from your sight.\r
\rIt appears that no one lives here.\r
\rYou see a machine with an android head and a cyber helmet.\r
\rYou are tied up and can't move.\r
\rYou see your party tied up and free them.\r
\rThere is a balcony out of reach high above.\r
